##############################################################################
 Overview.
##############################################################################

 Welcome to uMPS! 

 uMPS is a complete virtual machine simulator based around MIPS R2/3000
microprocessor.  

##############################################################################
 Description.
##############################################################################
 
 It features a full-fledged graphic user interface running under X Window,
complete sources and PDF documentation.

 It has been successfully ported on GNU/Linux, *BSD, SUN Solaris UNIX and MacOSX
platforms.

 The src directory contains the full sources of the simulator; other
directories contain support files and simple examples.

 For any question, contact the author: mmorsian@users.sourceforge.net

##############################################################################
 Some hints.
##############################################################################

 Standard installation is described in ./INSTALL.
 It expects to find XForms, Libelf, and CrossCompiler sets into the GNU/Linux
standard locations.

 XForms -> /usr/X11R6/lib or /usr/lib
 Libelf -> /usr/include/lib 
 CrossCompiler(s) -> /usr/local/bin

 If you wanna use external libs or crosscompilers you have to specify their
path using configure options.
 Look at ./configure --help for more informations.
